HEADWORD: Omnivora
<hw>Om*niv"o*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Omnivorous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of ungulate
mammals including the hog and the hippopotamus. The term is also
sometimes applied to the bears, and to certain passerine
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

